# Trivy misconfiguration suppressions for the CI `trivy-scan` job.
# Each entry must state WHY the finding is intentional — bare IDs rot.

# AVD-DS-0002 — "Specify at least 1 USER command with a non-root user".
# Intentional and load-bearing here: the devcontainer's ENTRYPOINT MUST run as
# root to configure the egress firewall (iptables) and the Squid TLS-bump proxy
# before any dev session exists. Privileges are not held for dev work — the
# container image ships a non-root `dev` user (UID 1000, sudo intentionally
# absent) and all dev sessions enter via `container exec` as that user (see
# sandbox/.devcontainer/entrypoint.sh header). A `USER dev` line would break the
# privileged setup that is this repo's entire purpose.
AVD-DS-0002
